How I would judge whether V2 deserves promotion

I would not promote it merely because it contains more transformer flourishes. I would look for:

Higher top-1 accuracy on the same Gold file
Higher macro-F1, particularly for rare codes
Positive pre/post reranker gain
Lower NAICS ECE
Improved weak-SOC-group performance
Useful conformal coverage with manageable set sizes
No deterioration in adaptive exact or dictionary performance
Acceptable runtime

A reasonable result would be a modest overall top-1 gain accompanied by a larger gain on model-only rows and weak SOC groups. The full top-1-to-top-4 gap is an upper bound, not a promise.

